Both required outputs are written. 25 iterations, 100 hypotheses, 100 statistical analyses tested.

**Key findings:**
- **Dominant prognostic signals:** ECOG-PS (β = -1.16 mo/unit), mCRPC (-0.52 mo), log10(PSA) (-0.80 mo/log), albumin (+0.49 mo/g/dL), weight loss (-0.075 mo/%), LDH and alk-phos.
- **Central interaction:** brca2_mutation × treatment_olaparib is strongly positive (β ≈ +1.45 mo, p ≈ 0); BRCA2+ patients gain +1.55 mo on olaparib while BRCA2- patients do not benefit.
- **Refuted "expected" interactions:** PSMA-high × Lu177-PSMA, MSI-high × pembrolizumab, AR-V7 × enzalutamide all null in this cohort.
- **No demographic disparities** detected on PFS (race, insurance, rural).
- **SNP scan** found 1/25 with p<0.05, consistent with chance under multiple testing.
